nciThesaurus.definition: A radioimmunoconjugate comprised of the humanized monoclonal antibody tacatuzumab, directed against alpha fetoprotein, that is conjugated to the chelating agent tetraxetan and radiolabeled with the beta-emitting radioisotope Yttrium Y 90. Yttrium Y 90 tacatuzumab tetraxetan binds to tumor cells expressing alpha fetoprotein, thereby selectively delivering a cytotoxic dose of beta radiation.
synonyms: Yttrium Y 90 DOTA Monoclonal Antibody HuAFP31
yttrium Y 90 DOTA monoclonal antibody HuAFP31
